## 3. CULTURAL INTELLIGENCE FRAMEWORK

Different cultures require different adaptations to achieve Flow.

| Region / Context | The Challenge (Mammon) | The Fix (Flow) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Western** (Individualist) | Over-medicalization & stigma | **Environmental Design:** Change the office, not the brain. |
| **East Asian** (Collectivist) | Pressure to conform/mask | **Safe Pockets:** Create micro-communities for unmasked authenticity. |
| **Global South** (Resource Constrained) | Scarcity & Survival mode | **Community Support:** Share resources to lower the collective baseline stress. |
| **Indigenous** (Traditional) | Colonial erasure of wisdom | **Integration:** Frame neurodivergence through traditional roles (e.g., the Seer/Shaman). |

